	 <para>The <application>&applet;</application> applet provides a convenient way to monitor connections to wireless devices.
		</para> 

    <sect2 id="wireless-introduction-add">
      <title>To Add &applet; to a Panel</title>
      <para>To add <application>&applet;</application> to a panel,
      right-click on the panel, then choose <guimenuitem>Add to
      Panel</guimenuitem>.  Select <application>&applet;</application>
      in the <application>Add to the panel</application> dialog, then
      click <guibutton>OK</guibutton>.</para>
        <para>The layout of the <application>&applet;</application> applet varies depending on the size and type of panel in which the applet resides.</para>
    </sect2>
  </sect1>

<!-- ================ Usage ================================ -->
  <sect1 id="wireless-usage"> 
	 <title>Usage</title> 
	 <para>When no wireless device has a connection, the &applet; displays the text <literal>NA</literal>, and the applet boxes are transparent.</para>
	 <para>When a wireless device has a connection, the &applet; displays the text <literal>Wi Fi</literal>. The color of the boxes in the panel applet indicates whether a link is established, as follows:</para>
         <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
             <term>Green</term>
             <listitem>
               <para>The wireless device has established a link.</para>
               <para>The strength of the link is indicated by the number of green boxes: the greater the number of green boxes, the stronger the link.</para>
             </listitem>
           </varlistentry>
           <varlistentry>
             <term>Red</term>
             <listitem>
               <para>The wireless device has not established a link.</para>
             </listitem>
           </varlistentry>
         </variablelist>
	 <para>You can also display the signal strength as a percentage. For more information on how to configure &applet; to show the signal strength as a percentage, see <xref linkend="wireless-prefs"/>.</para>
	 <para>Each instance of &applet; can monitor only one wireless device. You must start an instance of &applet; for each wireless device that you want to monitor.
</para>
  </sect1>

<!-- ============= Customization ============================= -->
<!-- Use this section to describe how to customize the applet. -->
  <sect1 id="wireless-prefs"> 
	 <title>Settings</title> 
	 <para>To configure <application>&applet;</application>, right-click on the applet, then choose <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>.</para> 
	 <para>The <guimenuitem>Wireless Link Monitor Preferences</guimenuitem> dialog contains the following components: </para> 
	 <variablelist> 
	   <varlistentry> 
	     <term><guilabel>Monitored device</guilabel></term> 
	     <listitem> 
	       <para>Use this drop-down list to select the wireless device that you want to monitor.</para> 
	     </listitem> 
	   </varlistentry> 
	   <varlistentry> 
	     <term><guilabel>Show signal strength in percentage</guilabel></term> 
	     <listitem> 
	       <para>Select this option to display the signal strength as a percentage. 
               </para> 
	     </listitem> 
	   </varlistentry> 
	 </variablelist>
  </sect1>

